  "texts": [
    "First, ALBATROSS may underestimate the impact of solvation effects on charged amino acids.",
    "Second, ALBATROSS does not account for transient secondary structure elements, a pervasive source of local conformational heterogeneity in many IDRs, which may bias predictions for IDRs rich in transient helicity to be too expanded.",
    "Finally, we likely underestimate the hydrophobic effect for aliphatic residues, an intrinsically challenging phenomenon to capture in coarse-grained force fields for IDR simulations.",
    "These two final points mean that we likely overestimate the predicted dimensions of IDRs that possess hydrophobicity-driven secondary structures, a caveat that should be carefully considered for IDRs enriched for helicity-promoting and/or aliphatic residues.",
    "The use of an LSTM-BRNN architecture enabled us to develop trained networks that were performant (10-50 sequences per second) on CPU commodity hardware."
